  "label": "Saltglass Quietroom",
  "description": "Saltglass Quietroom serves as a private sleeping chamber set off the inward-facing plan of Saltglass Courtyard House. Basalt walls finished in pale mineral wash carry shallow buttress ribs that stiffen the room against the city’s measurable tidal stresses. A high slit aperture, screened by layered baffles and shutters, admits the courtyard’s saltglass-diffused light as a steady, glare-muted illumination. Built-in stone shelving and a low sleeping platform are cut directly from the wall mass, leaving the floor clear and easily kept free of mineral haze grit.",
